Package ohos.utils.net

Class UrlQueryFilter

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.utils.net.UrlQueryFilter

  • public class UrlQueryFilter
extends Object
    Provides basic URL query analysis capabilities, including filtering invalid characters and obtaining query parameter pairs.

    A simple example is as follows: 

     UrlQueryFilter urlFilter = new UrlQueryFilter();
 String url = "http://www.xxx:port/xxxx/xxxx?name=tom&name=lily&age=20";
 urlFilter.parseUrl(url);
    Since:
    4

      • setFirstPriority

        public void setFirstPriority​(boolean value)
        Sets the value priority for duplicate keys in a query parameter pair.

        If value is set to true, the value matching the first key has the top priority. If value is false (default setting), the value matching the last key has the top priority.

        Parameters:
        value - Specifies whether the value matching the first key has the top priority if there are duplicate keys in the parameter pair.
        Since:
        4

      • getFirstPriority

        Checks whether the value matching the first one of duplicate keys in the parameter pair has the top priority.
        Returns:

        4

      • parseParamPair

        protected void parseParamPair​(String name,
                              String value)
        Parses an escaped query parameter pair.

        This method can be overloaded. By default, the escaped parameter pair uses the ValueFilter of its key to filter its value. The filtered parameter pair is stored in the internal Map and List objects.

        Parameters:
        name - Indicates the key of the query parameter pair to parse.
        value - Indicates the value of the query parameter pair to parse.
        Since:
        5

      • addParams

        protected void addParams​(Pair<String,String> entry)
        Adds a filtered parameter key-value pair to the internal List and Map objects.

        If the value parameter passed to the setFirstPriority(boolean) method is set to true, the value matching the first added key is used in the event of duplicate keys; otherwise, the value matching the last added key takes effect.

        Parameters:
        entry - Indicates the parameter key-value pair to add after filtering.
        Since:
        5
